;
; symrec_tie_1 -- DETERMINISM WITNESS (the (F) landing's gate 1b,
; KeyedInstances.md sec 0.6.5). The two recursive arms are STRUCTURALLY
; SYMMETRIC: same shape, same base relation (edge), same output vars --
; so their inductive views tie on BOTH the structural hash and the
; first-column-id comparator levels, and only the det_seq stamp (the
; ForEachView-order total key) orders them. Before the (F) landing this
; program's emitted .ir/.h permuted run to run (2 distinct hashes / 6
; runs); it must stay byte-stable forever. A regression here means a
; pointer-ordered iteration crept back into an emission-visible path.

#message edge(u64 A, u64 B).
#local tc(u64 A, u64 B).
#query out(free u64 A, free u64 B).

tc(A, B) : edge(A, B).
tc(A, B) : tc(A, X), edge(X, B).
tc(A, B) : edge(A, X), tc(X, B).

out(A, B) : tc(A, B).
